#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:6
msgid "Working with the Attribute Table"
msgstr "Rad sa atributskom tabelom"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:8
msgid ""
"The attribute table displays information on features of a selected layer. "
"Each row in the table represents a feature (with or without geometry), and "
"each column contains a particular piece of information about the feature. "
"Features in the table can be searched, selected, moved or even edited."
msgstr ""
"Atributska tabela prikazuje informacije o objektima izabranog sloja. Svaki "
"red u tabeli predstavlja objekat (sa geometrijom ili bez nje), a svaka "
"kolona sadrži određenu informaciju o objektu. Objekti u tabeli mogu se "
"pretraživati, birati, pomerati ili čak uređivati."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:22
msgid "Foreword: Spatial and non-spatial tables"
msgstr "Uvod: prostorne i neprostorne tabele"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:24
msgid ""
"QGIS allows you to load spatial and non-spatial layers. This currently "
"includes tables supported by GDAL and delimited text, as well as the "
"PostgreSQL, MS SQL Server, SpatiaLite and Oracle providers. All loaded "
"layers are listed in the :guilabel:`Layers` panel. Whether a layer is "
"spatially enabled or not determines whether you can interact with it on the "
"map."
msgstr ""
"QGIS vam omogućava da učitate prostorne i neprostorne slojeve. Ovo trenutno "
"uključuje tabele koje podržavaju GDAL i razdvojen tekst, kao i PostgreSQL, "
"MS SQL Server, SpatiaLite i Oracle provajdere. Svi učitani slojevi navedeni "
"su u panelu :guilabel:`Slojevi`. To da li je sloj prostorno omogućen ili ne "
"određuje da li možete da komunicirate s njim na karti."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:30
msgid ""
"Non-spatial tables can be browsed and edited using the attribute table view."
" Furthermore, they can be used for field lookups. For example, you can use "
"columns of a non-spatial table to define attribute values, or a range of "
"values that are allowed, to be added to a specific vector layer during "
"digitizing. Have a closer look at the edit widget in section "
":ref:`vector_attributes_menu` to find out more."
msgstr ""
"Neprostorne tabele mogu se pregledati i uređivati pomoću prikaza atributske "
"tabele. Osim toga, mogu se koristiti za pretraživanje polja. Na primer, "
"možete koristiti kolone neprostorne tabele da definišete vrednosti atributa,"
" ili opseg dozvoljenih vrednosti, koje se dodaju određenom vektorskom sloju "
"tokom digitalizovanja. Pogledajte pobliže vidžet za uređivanje u odeljku "
":ref:`vector_attributes_menu` da biste saznali više."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:40
msgid "Introducing the attribute table interface"
msgstr "Predstavljanje interfejsa atributske tabele"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:42
msgid ""
"To open the attribute table for a vector layer, activate the layer by "
"clicking on it in the :ref:`label_legend`. Then, from the main "
":menuselection:`Layer` menu, choose |openTable| :menuselection:`Open "
"Attribute Table`. It is also possible to right-click on the layer and choose"
" |openTable| :menuselection:`Open Attribute Table` from the drop-down menu, "
"or to click on the |openTable| :guilabel:`Open Attribute Table` button in "
"the Attributes toolbar. If you prefer shortcuts, :kbd:`F6` will open the "
"attribute table. :kbd:`Shift+F6` will open the attribute table filtered to "
"selected features and :kbd:`Ctrl+F6` will open the attribute table filtered "
"to visible features."
msgstr ""
"Da biste otvorili atributsku tabelu za vektorski sloj, aktivirajte sloj "
"klikom na njega u :ref:`label_legend`. Zatim iz glavnog menija "
":menuselection:`Sloj` izaberite |openTable| :menuselection:`Otvori "
"atributsku tabelu`. Takođe je moguće kliknuti desnim tasterom na sloj i "
"izabrati |openTable| :menuselection:`Otvori atributsku tabelu` iz padajućeg "
"menija, ili kliknuti na dugme |openTable| :guilabel:`Otvori atributsku "
"tabelu` u paleti alatki Atributi. Ako preferirate prečice, :kbd:`F6` će "
"otvoriti atributsku tabelu. :kbd:`Shift+F6` će otvoriti atributsku tabelu "
"filtriranu na izabrane objekte, a :kbd:`Ctrl+F6` će otvoriti atributsku "
"tabelu filtriranu na vidljive objekte."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:865
msgid "openTable"
msgstr "openTable"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/working_with_vector/attribute_table.rst:53
msgid ""
"This will open a new window that displays the feature attributes for the "
"layer (figure_attributes_table_). According to the setting in "
":menuselection:`Settings --> Options --> Data sources` menu, the attribute "
"table will open in a docked window or a regular window. The total number of "
"features in the layer and the number of currently selected/filtered features"
" are shown in the attribute table title, as well as if the layer is "
"spatially limited."
msgstr ""
"Time će se otvoriti novi prozor koji prikazuje atribute objekata sloja "
"(figure_attributes_table_). Prema podešavanju u meniju "
":menuselection:`Podešavanja --> Opcije --> Izvori podataka`, atributska "
"tabela će se otvoriti u usidrenom prozoru ili običnom prozoru. Ukupan broj "
"objekata u sloju i broj trenutno izabranih/filtriranih objekata prikazani su"
" u naslovu atributske tabele, kao i da li je sloj prostorno ograničen."

